# Prediction Data Completeness

Predictions are only as good as the aligned panel. **Missing or corrupted data must be fixed at ingest/panel level ‚Äî not worked around in model code** (dropping columns, zero-filling, suppressing warnings).

## Before changing tracks, equations, or gates

1. Run `python scripts/audit_prediction_data.py --days 500` and check `pinned_missing_or_sparse`.
2. Read `prediction_data_requirements.py` ‚Äî `REQUIRED_COLD_DATASETS`, `PANEL_DERIVED_FACTORS`, `_PINNED_FOR_AUDIT`.
3. Confirm `load_aligned_factor_history(days=500)` has ‚â•45% coverage and non-zero std for pinned factors.

## Panel invariants (never break)

| Rule | Why |
|------|-----|
| **Daily beats annual** | `history_panel._join_annual_macro_by_year` must not replace daily columns (e.g. `usd_inr`) with annual snapshots ‚Äî fill NaN only |
| **Derived follows parent** | `usd_inr_momentum_5d`, `us_10y_velocity_3d` etc. are computed from parent series ‚Äî fix parent first |
| **Live vs panel parity** | Live snapshot (`macro_global`) and training panel must use the same factor semantics |

## Pinned factors (must have ‚â•45% coverage, non-zero variance in 500d window)

`oil_brent`, `usd_inr`, `sp500`, `us_10y`, `india_vix`, `fii_net_5d`, `dii_net_5d`, `nifty_pcr`, `repo_rate`, `nifty_pe`

## When adding a new factor

1. Add to `MACRO_FACTOR_KEYS` / track exog list only after cold-tier or derived path exists.
2. Document source in `REQUIRED_COLD_DATASETS` or `PANEL_DERIVED_FACTORS`.
3. Verify with audit script ‚Äî do not ship if coverage <45% unless explicitly experimental and gated.

